<subSubSection id="598F44A4CE78FFC0FF01CC425EF450D6" pageId="5" type="key">
<key id="6504401ECE78FFC0FF01CC425EF450D6" pageId="5">
<keyStep id="AA610F8ACE78FFC0FF01CC425EF451A0" pageId="5">
<paragraph id="112A172FCE78FFC0FF01CC425EF452DD" blockId="5.[132,1236,361,1023]" pageId="5">
<keyLead id="AA64B41ACE78FFC0FF01CC425EF452DD" pageId="5">1.Integument of mesoscutum and mesoscutellum smooth and shiny; preoccipital carina absent; transscutal sulcus between axillae shallowly impressed; mesoscutellum comparatively flat and low, acutely rounded apically in profile and slightly raised above level of metanotum.................................................................2</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="112A172FCE78FFC0FF01CCD45EF451A0" blockId="5.[132,1236,361,1023]" pageId="5">
<keyLead id="AA64B41ACE78FFC0FF01CCD45EF451A0" pageId="5">—Integument of mesoscutum and mesoscutellum matt, microalveolate to tessellate; preoccipital carina present at least laterally, sometimes weakly so; transscutal sulcus between axillae deeply and broadly impressed; mesoscutellum gently convex, broadly rounded apically in profile and distinctly raised above level of metanotum.............................. 3</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep id="AA610F8ACE78FFC0FF01CFBF5EF45040" pageId="5">
<paragraph id="112A172FCE78FFC0FF01CFBF5EF451D0" blockId="5.[132,1236,361,1023]" pageId="5">
<keyLead id="AA64B41ACE78FFC0FF01CFBF5EF451D0" pageId="5">
2.Malar space as long as 2× flagellar diameter; posterior margin of metatibia gently arched, without projection at distal angle; parapenicillum curved but not greatly sinuate; head width 1.0 mm or greater........................................ 
<taxonomicName id="D6956CACCE78FFC0FC6DCFCB5EF451D0" authority="Moure" authorityName="Moure" authorityYear="1950" box="[1000,1236,735,761]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Leurotrigona" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="5" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="23E1CB3DCE78FFC0FC6DCFCB5E5D51D0" box="[1000,1149,736,761]" italics="true" pageId="5">Leurotrigona</emphasis>
Moure
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="112A172FCE78FFC0FF01CE2E5EF45040" blockId="5.[132,1236,361,1023]" pageId="5">
<keyLead id="AA64B41ACE78FFC0FF01CE2E5EF45040" pageId="5">
—Malar space as long as flagellar diameter; posterior margin of metatibia somewhat sinuous, with distal angle projected; parapenicillum markedly sinuate; head width less than 1.0 mm........................................ 
<taxonomicName id="D6956CACCE78FFC0FCDECE645E235040" authority="Engel &amp; Rozen &amp; Sepúlveda-Cano &amp; Smith &amp; Thomas &amp; Ospina-Torres &amp; Gonzalez, 2019" authorityName="Engel &amp; Rozen &amp; Sepúlveda-Cano &amp; Smith &amp; Thomas &amp; Ospina-Torres &amp; Gonzalez" authorityYear="2019" box="[859,1027,847,873]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Trigonisca" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="5" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" status="new subgenus" subGenus="Exochotrigona">
<emphasis id="23E1CB3DCE78FFC0FCDECE645E235040" box="[859,1027,847,873]" italics="true" pageId="5">Exochotrigona</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Engel, 
<taxonomicNameLabel id="38D27646CE78FFC0FBD9CE645EF45040" box="[1116,1236,847,873]" pageId="5" rank="subGenus">n. subgen.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep id="AA610F8ACE78FFC0FF01CE5F5EF450D6" pageId="5">
<paragraph id="112A172FCE78FFC0FF01CE5F5EF4509D" blockId="5.[132,1236,361,1023]" pageId="5">
<keyLead id="AA64B41ACE78FFC0FF01CE5F5EF4509D" pageId="5">
3.Labrum simple; bristles along posterior margin of metatibia as long as or shorter than maximum metatibial width....................................... 
<taxonomicName id="D6956CACCE78FFC0FC46CEB15EB3509D" authority="Moure" authorityName="Moure" authorityYear="1950" box="[963,1171,922,948]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Trigonisca" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="5" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" sensu="stricto">
<emphasis id="23E1CB3DCE78FFC0FC46CEB15E1A509A" box="[963,1082,922,947]" italics="true" pageId="5">Trigonisca</emphasis>
Moure
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicNameLabel id="38D27646CE78FFC0FB1ACEB15EF4509D" box="[1183,1236,922,948]" pageId="5" sensu="stricto">s.str.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="112A172FCE78FFC0FF01CE945EF450D6" blockId="5.[132,1236,361,1023]" pageId="5">
<keyLead id="AA64B41ACE78FFC0FF01CE945EF450D6" pageId="5">
—Labrum bituberculate; bristles along posterior margin of metatibia distinctly longer than maximum metatibial width...................................... 
<taxonomicName id="D6956CACCE78FFC0FC7FCECF5EF450D6" authority="Moure" authorityName="Moure" authorityYear="1950" box="[1018,1236,996,1023]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Celetrigona" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="5" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="23E1CB3DCE78FFC0FC7FCECF5E5E50D7" box="[1018,1150,996,1022]" italics="true" pageId="5">Celetrigona</emphasis>
Moure
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
